    "title": "System Repair Update",
    "summary": "Adds system repair update option that preserves user data (games, saves, wallet, Wi-Fi profiles, controller configs, SSH keys) when updating an existing OkamaOS installation. Also updates installer with detection and backup/restore functions.",
    "notes": [
      "okama-install --repair-update preserves user data during OS reinstallation.",
      "okama-install --detect-existing-os checks for existing installations on target disk.",
      "Settings > Install/Persistence now auto-detects existing OS and shows Repair Update option.",
      "Repair Update selection screen lists disks with existing OS and allows one-press update.",
      "All user data paths are preserved: games, saves, wallet, downloads, Wi-Fi, configs, SSH keys.",
      "Install state tracks update history with UPDATED_FROM and UPDATED_AT fields.",
      "Bump: VERSION 2.1.2 -> 2.2.0."
    ],
